    <note>Chen(1) Jiang [28] After receiving the jinshi, he passed the imperial decree exam in 1007 in first place. According to some sources, Jiang moved from Xinghua jun, Putian county to Suzhou and established the Wuxian branch of the clan. However, others date the move with Tong and, since all the jinshi from Jiang's sons Dongzhi [3091] and Yuezhi are listed as Putian jinshi and none as Wuxian jinshi, I date the move with Tong [7129] and treat his grandsons Si [86] and Mu [3077] as Putian residents and Tong and his descendants as Wuxian residents. Jiang was Yangong's [102] and Yanwu's [103] great grandfather. Fujian TZ, 147.5a, 7a; Guangdong TZ, 14.21b; Suzhou FZ, 77.14b. CBD, 3, 2490.</note>
